    "body": "Some parts of starship are faster and some are less fast, though I admit the text website might be a bit hyperbolic.\r\nSince typically, starship has worse integration with a given shell, it may not always offer the same level due to the lack of things like async prompt rendering.\r\nGit status performance has been a pain point, and already improved a great deal since the switch from libgit2. It should also be somewhat improved with the most recent release, and in the future a gitoxide-based status could improve it further. FWIW will no longer `clone` as often on high-core systems, but it that should already be reflected in the current linked benchmark results.",
